<div style="border:solid 1px #999999; background:#f2f2c2; padding:5px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h4 id="toc0"><span>NOTICE FROM THE FOUNDATION RECORDS AND INFORMATION SECURITY ADMINISTRATION</span></h4>
<p>This document is currently pending SCP designation and research team assignment. If you are not assigned to this item or have selected this file in error, please exit without saving.</p>
<p>Please review the attached document for currently known information regarding the object.</p>
<p>&#8212; Alexis Rose, Digitization Department Lead</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="code">
<pre>
<code>**Item #:** SCP-XXXX (Pending designation)

**Object Class:** Safe (Likely designation)

**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-XXXX is currently held in a hermetically sealed 
Secure Object Container within Site-55's Low-Risk Objects Locker.
****PLEASE READ OVERSEER NOTE!!!!****

**Description:** Description of the item and its properties.

NOTICE
Please remember to replace all XXXX with the item's assigned number once it is available.
Additionally, please delete this message once the document is finalized.
Thank you.
- A. R.</code>
</pre></div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">📎&nbsp;ACCESS&nbsp;RAISA-6147&nbsp;(1722-1851)&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;📎&nbsp;CLOSE&nbsp;DOCUMENT</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">RAISA FILE: PRECURSOR GROUP [DEFUNCT]</span></strong><br />
<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">His/Her Majesty's Royal Foundation For The Study of Curiosities and Paranormal</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>FILE CREATED:</strong> c. 1722<br />
<strong>FILE LAST REVISED BY GROUP:</strong> c. 1851<br />
<strong>FILE RECOVERED:</strong> July 1946<br />
<strong>[TEXT REPRODUCED BELOW]</strong><sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup></p>
</blockquote>
<div class="c_content">
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/raisa-6147/coat.png" alt="coat.png" class="image" />
<hr />
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="font-size:175%;">BY DECREE OF HIS ROYAL MAJESTY KING GEORGE, RULER OF THESE UNITED KINGDOMS OF GREAT BRITAIN AND IRELAND, THIS DOCUMENT AND ITS CONTENTS ARE TO BE HELD IN SECRECY, AND USED TO PROTECT AND FURTHER THE INTERESTS OF THE BRITISH EMPIRE.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:300%;">GOD SAVE THE KING</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<hr />
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="font-size:200%;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">The WILL OF THE SANDS</span></span></p>
</div>
<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span>
<h1 id="toc1"><span>Paranormal Object</span></h1>
<p>A Saharan weapon from the age of barbirism and paganism, resembling a curved axe decorated with jewels of the desert.</p>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc2"><span>Threat Posed</span></h1>
<p>Benign</p>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc3"><span>Origins</span></h1>
<p>Believed to have been created by North-Saharan witchcraft before the modern age. The object was seized from the Order of Solomon's Temple<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-2')">2</a></sup> following the Illuminatus Schism<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-3" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-3')">3</a></sup>.</p>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc4"><span>Alchemist Asserstion</span></h1>
<p>The object is made of gold but radiates with the same energy of lead. Grandmaster Alchemists are to handle the object exclusively.</p>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc5"><span>Abnormality</span></h1>
<p>Records of the Order of Solomon's Temple utilizing the object to wage war during The Crusades is referenced in The Library. Though the object lacks the sharp edge of a blade or the deadliness of a bullet, it conjured warriors from the sands of the desert.</p>
<p>In order to summon warriors, the blade must be satisfied with a witchcraft ritual, the likes of which are described henceforth.</p>
<ol>
<li>Slit the throat of an adult male oxen and collect its spilled blood.</li>
<li>Collect the manure of a riverbeast<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-4" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-4')">4</a></sup>.</li>
<li>Finely grind lavender blossom into oil.</li>
<li>Gather fresh honey.</li>
<li>Mix into a concoction using a wooden ladle and roasting over a cast iron pot.</li>
<li>Bathe the object in the concoction, storing the rest.</li>
<li>Present the blade to the sands.</li>
</ol>
<p>The summoned do not understand the King's English, but obey the language of Kemet. Commands may be issued exclusively in the language. One must not be fluent, but understandable enough for the summoned to obey.<br /></p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><span style="font-size:25%;">PAGE 1 OF 3<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-5" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-5')">5</a></sup></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span>
<div class="c_content">
<div style="text-align: right;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/raisa-6147/coat.png" style="width:10%;" alt="coat.png" class="image" /></div>
<h1 id="toc6"><span>APPEARNCES</span></h1>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/raisa-6147/khopesh.png" style="width:45%;" alt="khopesh.png" class="image" /><br />
<span style="font-size:75%;">Depiction of King Ozymandias<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-6" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-6')">6</a></sup> using the object to conquer and expand the Kemet Empire.<br />
Obtained from the Order of Solomon's Temple.</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/raisa-6147/blades.png" style="width:20%;" alt="blades.png" class="image" /><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="font-size:75%;">Illustration of both sides of the object.</span></div>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc7"><span>APPLICATIONS</span></h1>
<p>The object has been used to assist in the pacification of the savages of the Indies and Arabia. Due to the abscence of riverbeasts in these lands, its use is sparing but successful.<br /></p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><span style="font-size:25%;">PAGE 2 OF 3</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-1')">1</a>. [RAISA NOTICE] Edits have been made for spelling, grammar, and general formatting.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-2')">2</a>. [RAISA NOTICE] An organization dedicated to the containment of the abnormalities. Defunct c.1720</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-3"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-3')">3</a>. [RAISA NOTICE] This is believed to be in reference to the Fifth Occult War.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-4"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-4')">4</a>. [RAISA NOTICE] Colloquial term for 'hippopotamus'.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-5"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-5')">5</a>. [RAISA NOTICE] The location of the third page of this document is currently unknown, and its contents undocumented.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-6"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-6')">6</a>. [RAISA NOTICE] Known as Ramesses II</div>
</div>
</div>
