<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">📎&nbsp;ACCESS&nbsp;RAISA-6147&nbsp;(1944)&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;📎&nbsp;CLOSE&nbsp;DOCUMENT</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">RAISA FILE: PRECURSOR GROUP [DEFUNCT]</span></strong><br />
<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">His/Her Majesty's Royal Foundation For The Study of Curiosities and Paranormal</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>FILE CREATED:</strong> c. 1921<br />
<strong>FILE LAST REVISED BY GROUP:</strong> c. 1945 [UPDATED]<br />
<strong>FILE RECOVERED:</strong> July 1946<br />
<strong>[TEXT REPRODUCED BELOW]</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<div style="border:1px solid #000000;">
<div style="color:black; background: #ededed;padding: 15px;">
<div style="text-align: right;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/raisa-6147/coat.png" style="width:10%;" alt="coat.png" class="image" /></div>
<hr />
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><tt><strong>BY DECREE OF HIS ROYAL MAJESTY KING GEORGE VI, RULER OF THESE UNITED KINGDOMS OF GREAT BRITAIN AND IRELAND, THIS DOCUMENT AND ITS CONTENTS ARE TO BE HELD IN SECRECY, AND USED TO PROTECT AND FURTHER THE INTERESTS OF THE BRITISH EMPIRE.</strong></tt></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><tt><strong>GOD SAVE THE KING.</strong></tt></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<hr />
<p><tt><strong>Designation-</strong> AO-023</tt></p>
<p><tt><strong>Threat-</strong> None</tt></p>
<p><tt><strong>Classifications-</strong> Object, Inert, Thaumaturgic, Ritualistic, Artifact, Conjurative, Location-Dependant, Weapon, Golem</tt></p>
<p><tt><strong>Stored-</strong> Hall 98, Container 23-C</tt></p>
<p><tt><strong>Identifiers-</strong> Gold coloured hopesh decorated with electrum patterns and turquoise gemstone along the sides and hilt. Measures 45cm in length. Appears to have been made for aesthetics over practicality.</tt><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/raisa-6147/khopesh.jpg" style="width:45%;" alt="khopesh.jpg" class="image" /><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="font-size:75%;"><tt>Affectionately named 'The Will of the Sands.'</tt></span></div>
<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span>
<p><tt><strong>Abnormality-</strong> Abnormal properties activated via ritual, is otherwise unremarkable. If the ritual is followed (as detailed in attached document A-23) the object will create sand golems resembling humans, all capable of combat. Number of golems created is directly correlated to the amount of sand immediately available.</tt></p>
<p><tt><strong>History-</strong> Acquired from the now defunct Order of Solomon's Temple, whom possibly acquired the object from the Frumentarii. Originated in ancient Egypt via believed thaumaturgic/alchemic means. Used to assist in the conquest of rival armies. No documented records of the object's use exist outside of His Majesty's Foundation.</tt></p>
</div>
</div>
<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span>
<div style="border:1px solid #000000;">
<div style="color:black; background: #ededed;padding: 15px;">
<div style="text-align: right;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/raisa-6147/coat.png" style="width:10%;" alt="coat.png" class="image" /></div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><tt><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">PROPOSAL: USE OF ANOMALOUS OBJECT 023</span></strong></tt></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<tt>Most esteemed gentlemen of the Operations Council,</tt></p>
<p><tt>Intelligence operatives have revealed the Kingdom of Italy and the Deutsches Reich intend on allying sometime in early September.</tt></p>
<p><tt>With most of our weapons and manpower being reallocated, our African protectorates are soon to be under immediate Italian threat. Moving the requisite amount of troops to defend our interests will consume far too many resources which would be better spent elsewhere, as well as time we cannot afford to lose.</tt></p>
<p><tt>It is for the above reasons I would propose the use of AO-023 on a mass scale to create an army which may fulfill our needs. The materials required to satisfy the object's ritualistic cost are affordable when compared to steel, iron, and other items which will surely only become more expensive as the war continues.</tt></p>
<p><tt>Though the limitations of these soldiers are very rudimentary, they will require our enemy to expend bullets, manpower, and other resources of their own to combat them. As these conjured soldiers are golems, they require no sustenance and will blindly obey our commands as issued to them. We may not be able to overpower our opponents, but we can easily succeed in a war of attrition by using this object. The possibility of the Ahnenerbe Obskuracorps possessing knowledge of AO-023 is minimal, as most documentation regarding the object was burned or acquired by His Majesty's Foundation following the Fifth Occult War.</tt></p>
<p><tt>I thank you for overseeing this proposal.</tt><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><tt>- Edward Basil</tt></p>
</div>
<br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><span style="font-size:30%;">DO NOT WRITE BELOW THIS LINE, OFFICIAL USE ONLY.</span></p>
<hr />
<p><em><span style="font-family: 'Reenie Beanie'; font-size: 30px; color:blue">Proposal approved.</span></em><span style="font-family: 'Reenie Beanie'; font-size: 30px; color:blue"><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
- Chamberlains 1,3, 4, and 5.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">NOTICE&nbsp;FROM&nbsp;SITE-55&nbsp;DEFENSE&nbsp;OVERSEER</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;CLOSE&nbsp;NOTICE</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<div style="background: url(http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/the-great-hippo/scp_trans.png) center no-repeat ; float: center; border: solid 2px #000000; padding: 1px 15px; box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h2 id="toc8"><span><strong>FROM THE DESK OF DEFENSE OVERSEER CHAMBERS,</strong></span></h2>
<hr />
<p><strong>To whom it may concern,</strong></p>
<p><strong>The SCP classification of this item is to be expedited under official directorial orders. Following its classification, MTF-Lambda 7 Captain Hart is to be allowed access to the item for the explicit purposes of site defense, and a stock of the mixture needed to activate the item is to be kept ready for use at all times.</strong></p>
<p><strong>The Insurgency has grown bold with their recent incursions, and guard personnel are at an all-time low, but they cannot overcome the sands of the Mojave.</strong></p>
<p><strong>-C.C</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
